title: Alphabet, Google’s Parent Company, Reports 27% Drop in Profit
description: Google’s parent company reported earnings that were below analysts’ expectations, bringing in $13.9 billion in profit on $69.1 billion in sales.
dc:creator: Nico Grant
media:credit: Laura Morton for The New York Times
media:description: The headquarters of Google and its parent company Alphabet Inc. in Mountain View, Calif.
